Measures -> security policies and security mechanisms
Policy is a statement of what is and is not allowed.
used as the operational definition of "security" in a given context
Mechanisms are the means by which policies are enforced.
can be methods, tools, or procedures
detect attackers who violate security policy
prevent attackers from violating security policy
- prevent attacks, then assess + repair damage
- prevent disruptions to service despite attacks
Policies and mechanisms depend on assumptions and trust.
